1. What does the “msconfig” command do?
msconfig opens the System Configuration utility, which lets you manage startup programs, services, boot options, and troubleshoot system issues.

2. What is the purpose of the “cmd” command?
cmd launches the Command Prompt, a command-line interpreter for executing commands, scripts, and troubleshooting tasks in Windows.

3. What settings are shown on the right side of the screen?
The right pane displays network adapter details for a Realtek Gaming GbE Family Controller, including:
    - DNS server assignment: Automatic (DHCP)
    - Manufacturer: Realtek
    - Description: Realtek Gaming GbE Family Controller
    - Driver version: 1168.18.312.2024
    - Physical address (MAC): E0-73-E7-CE-2E-CC.

